TITLE: Could polls about battleground Senate races be wrong? Democrat, Republican strategists weigh in
SUMMARY: Democrat and Republican strategists weigh in on whether polls in Pennsylvania, Ohio, Georgia and Minnesota could be wrong in predicting Dem candidates winning in November

TITLE: Rubio: Migrants sent to Martha's Vineyard a 'minuscule fraction of the problem' facing border communities
SUMMARY: Sen. Marco Rubio said that while Martha's Vineyard is struggling with 50 migrants sent up north by Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis, border communities deal with much more.

TITLE: Zeldin vows to fire liberal Manhattan DA on 'day one,' rips Hochul's cashless bail support: 'Save this state'
SUMMARY: Republican New York gubernatorial candidate asked Democratic voters to help him “save this state,” as he promised to fire liberal Manhattan DA Alvin Bragg on “day one.”

TITLE: NY Gov. Hochul under fire for COVID-test Democrat donor deal week before absentee ballots sent out
SUMMARY: New York Gov. Kathy Hochul is implicated in an alleged “pay to play” scheme in which the state paid 45% more than California for rapid COVID tests from the same supplier.

TITLE: NYC Mayor Adams claims Texas Gov. Abbott 'refused to do any form of coordination' on migrant busing
SUMMARY: New York City Mayor Eric Adams claimed that Texas Gov. Greg Abbott "refused to do any form of coordination" regarding the busing of migrants from the southern border to the Big Apple.

TITLE: Yeshiva University suspends all campus clubs after Supreme Court denies bid to block LGBTQ+ group
SUMMARY: Yeshiva University, after the Supreme Court denied their attempt to block an LGBTQ+ club on campus, has suspended all campus groups while they seek other legal remedies.

TITLE: NYC Mayor Adams accuses GOP governors of sending migrant buses to distract from their 'human rights' abuses
SUMMARY: Democratic New York City Mayor Eric Adams claimed Republican Governors Greg Abbott and Ron DeSantis were sending migrants to other states because they are "covering up" their policies.

TITLE: El Paso mayor says city’s goal is to help bus migrants to their destinations, treat them like human beings
SUMMARY: El Paso Mayor Oscar Leeser said the city is helping bus migrants to their destinations in other parts of the U.S. as the border city continues to face an influx of migrants.

TITLE: Martha's Vineyard: Massachusetts governor solicits donations in migrant housing update
SUMMARY: Republican MA Gov. Charlie Baker provided an update on migrants flown to Martha's Vineyard, sharing a way for Americans to donate to the state while it houses the 50 migrants.

TITLE: Durbin says GOP governors of Florida, Texas and Arizona are ‘using migrants as pawns’
SUMMARY: Illinois Sen. Dick Durbin accused Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis, Texas Gov. Greg Abbott and Arizona Gov. Doug Ducey of using migrants as pawns for their political campaigns.

TITLE: Graham defends federal abortion bill amid criticism it tramples states’ rights
SUMMARY: Graham defended his federal abortion bill on "Fox News Sunday," saying he is "pro-life even in an election year" after some Republicans indicated they wouldn't support it.

TITLE: Obama, Martha's Vineyard celebs silent on opening up island homes to illegal immigrants
SUMMARY: Former President Obama and other affluent Martha's Vineyard Democrats did not respond when asked by Fox News if they would be open to housing migrants sent by GOP governors.

TITLE: Gavin Newsom-Ron DeSantis war of words a possible 2024 or 2028 preview
SUMMARY: Democratic Gov. Gavin Newsom of California and Republican Gov. Ron DeSantis of Florida are once in the spotlight this weekend, sparking more speculation about their 2024 intentions

TITLE: Trump, Obama invited to attend Washington, DC memorial service for Queen Elizabeth II
SUMMARY: All former surviving U.S. presidents have been invited to attend a memorial service for Queen Elizabeth II at the Washington National Cathedral in Washington, D.C.

TITLE: ICE arrests Ecuadorian illegal immigrant wanted on international warrant for alleged rape of 13-year-old girl
SUMMARY: ICE announced this week that it has arrested an Ecuadorian illegal immigrant with a warrant out for his arrest for the alleged rape of a 13-year-old girl.

TITLE: Iran's president says meeting with Biden not 'beneficial,' policies same as Trump
SUMMARY: Iranian President Ebrahim Raisi rejected meeting with President Biden to discuss a nuclear deal, saying his positions are the same as former President Trump's

TITLE: Trump attorneys given until Tuesday for response to DOJ motion on classified docs
SUMMARY: A court gave former President Trump's lawyers until Tuesday to respond to a DOJ request to continue to use classified documents seized from Mar-a-Lago.

TITLE: Trump holds Save America rally in Ohio supporting Senate candidate JD Vance
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump was speaking at a rally in Youngstown, Ohio on Saturday night in support of Republican Senate Candidate J.D. Vance.

TITLE: Gianno Caldwell says ending cash bail in Illinois will be like 'The Purge' after brother murdered in Chicago
SUMMARY: Fox News contributor Gianno Caldwell argued that Illinois eliminating cash bail is setting it up to operate like the cities in "The Purge" horror movies.

TITLE: Facing historic Biden-era border crisis, GOP governors go on the offensive
SUMMARY: Facing an enormous migrant wave coming through the southern border, Republican governors are taking increasingly aggressive moves of their own to counter the crisis.
